.TH "dbg_check_idx_size" 9 "dbg_check_idx_size" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dbg_check_idx_size \- check index size.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dbg_check_idx_size
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "long long idx_size "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "idx_size" 12
size to check
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function walks the UBIFS index, calculates its size and checks that the
size is equivalent to \fIidx_size\fP. Returns zero in case of success and a
negative error code in case of failure.
